  "why": "The paper goes beyond merely reporting counts of failures: it analyzes properties of discovered failures (state coverage, distinct crash types, spatial distribution of crash-triggering states, and a robustness/sensitivity measure) and compares how different methods concentrate failures (e.g., boundary vs. spread). These constitute partial diagnostic insight into failure patterns and correlations with input structure. However, the paper does not trace failures back to deeper underlying model vulnerabilities (e.g., corrupted/biased training data, spurious features, or overfitting) nor provide root-cause attributions; repairs rely on manual inspection to select corrective actions rather than automated diagnosis linking failures to specific model weaknesses. Therefore the paper provides characterization of failures but not explanations that link them to underlying vulnerabilities.",
